<1ST_LINE>u a AM-FamilySlayings     06-26 0163</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Family Slayings,0168</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Four Dead, 2-Year-Old Unharmed In Philly Murder-Suicide</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHILADELPHIA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man shot his wife, son and baby daughter
in the head before turning the gun on himself Saturday night, but
spared a 2-year-old daughter who survived the rampage uharmed,
police said.
   Winston Coghiel, 33, shot his 30-year-old wife, June, as she sat
on their living room couch, said police Lt. James Henwood.
   Coghiel then shot 3-year-old son Winston Jr. and 9-month-old
daughter Kimberley, who were also found in the living room, Henwood
said. The man then shot himself with the .38-caliber Browning
automatic.
   All four were dead of gunshot wounds to the head when family
members found them, the lieutenant said. There were no signs of a
struggle.
   The surviving daughter, Celeste, was not hurt, but was taken to
Children's Hospital, Henwood said. She was released later in the
evening.
   Family members told police that Coghiel had been depressed and
was convinced people were after him, Henwood said.
</TEXT>
