   Guerrilla activity was reported on the rise around Kabul, with
insurgents frequently moving within rocket range of the city.
Guerrillas claimed to have rocketed the airport last week but not
on the day reported by diplomats.
   Soviet forces entered Afghanistan in December 1979 to replace
one Marxist government with another and battle the anti-communist
insurgency. Soviet troops began withdrawing May 15 under the terms
of a United Nations-sponsored peace accord.
