<HEAD>Pakistani Foreign Minister's Car In Accident</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The car carrying Pakistani Foreign Minister
Sahabzada Yaqub-Khan crashed into the back of a Jeep on Sunday and
slightly injured a Chinese woman, Pakistani officials said.
   Yaqub-Khan expressed regret over the accident and concern for
the woman when he met later with Chinese Foreign Minister Qian
Qichen.
   Pakistan Embassy official Nisarullah Baluch said the jeep was
ahead of the foreign minister's convoy, which was driving from the
airport. The Jeep's driver misunderstood police signals to pull
over and instead stopped, and the foreign minister's car struck it
in the rear.
