Pakistan's President Mohammad Zia Ul-haq abruptly dissolved the
National Assembly and dismissed Prime Minister Mohammad Khan Junejo
and other ministers on May 29.
   Zia acted just as Junejo returned home from a trip to China.
   Yaqub-Khan, who resigned as foreign minister last year for
personal reasons, has resumed the post in a caretaker government
pending elections.
