Qian, he said the fact that his first visit in office was to China
showed the ``exception relationship'' between the two countries.
   Yaqub-Khan is scheduled to meet Monday with Chinese Premier Li
Peng. Topics are likely to include Afghanistan, where both
countries long have pushed for the current Soviet withdrawal.
   Li, who took office in April, has promised his first trip abroad
will be to Pakistan.
